<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/wms/2005-06-20.27WS.4" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/1682" speakername="Bridget Prentice" speakeroffice="The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Constitutional Affairs" colnum="27WS"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm200506/cmhansrd/cm050620/wmstext/50620m01.htm#50620m01.html_spmin1">
	<p pid=".27WS.4/1">The Secretary of State for Constitutional Affairs, Lord Falconer of Thoroton, has made the following written ministerial statement in the other place today:</p>
	<p pid=".27WS.4/2" class="indent">&quot;On <phrase class="date" code="2005-06-17">Friday 17 June</phrase> the Government published their response to the Constitutional Affairs Select Committee's report on the operation of the Special Immigration Appeals Commission (SIAC) and the use of special advocates. Copies have been placed in the Libraries of both Houses. The response is also available on the Department for Constitutional Affairs website.&quot;</p>
</speech>
